# 🌾 KisanMandi — Farmer's Market Price Aggregator

A full-stack web app for farmers and traders to track crop prices across local Karnataka markets.

---

## Project Structure

```
farmer-market-aggregator/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py          # FastAPI app + routes
│   ├── models.py        # SQLAlchemy DB models
│   ├── schemas.py       # Pydantic schemas
│   ├── crud.py          # Database operations
│   ├── database.py      # SQLite connection
│   └── requirements.txt
└── frontend/
    ├── public/
    │   └── index.html
    ├── src/
    │   ├── App.js
    │   ├── index.js
    │   ├── index.css
    │   ├── api.js
    │   └── pages/
    │       ├── Dashboard.js
    │       ├── Search.js
    │       ├── Trends.js
    │       ├── Submit.js
    │       └── Alerts.js
    └── package.json
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Backend (FastAPI + SQLite)

Open a terminal in VS Code and run:

```bash
cd backend

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Activate it
# On Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate
# On Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Start the server

cd D:\python\farmer_market_aggregator\backend
uvicorn main:app --reload

#uvicorn main:py --reload
```

The API will start at: **http://localhost:8000**

> 📌 The database `market_prices.db` is created automatically on first run.
> Demo data for Tomato, Potato, Onion, etc. is seeded automatically!

**API Docs (Swagger UI):** http://localhost:8000/docs

---

### 2. Frontend (React)

Open a **second terminal** in VS Code:

```bash
cd ..
cd frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the React dev server
npm start
```

The app will open at: **http://localhost:3000**

---

## 🚀 Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Dashboard** | Overview of all crops — avg, min, max prices + best markets |
| **Search** | Search any crop → see prices across all markets instantly |
| **Trends** | Interactive line chart of price history (7/14/30 days) |
| **Add Price** | Submit new price entries from any market |
| **Alerts** | Automatically detects price surges/drops ≥10% |

---

## 🔌 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/crops/` | List all crops |
| GET | `/markets/` | List all markets |
| GET | `/prices/search/?crop=Tomato` | Latest price per market |
| GET | `/prices/best/?crop=Tomato` | Best market for a crop |
| GET | `/prices/trends/?crop=Tomato&days=7` | Historical trend data |
| GET | `/summary/` | Crop summary stats |
| GET | `/alerts/` | Price movement alerts |
| POST | `/prices/` | Submit new price entry |
| DELETE | `/prices/{id}` | Delete a price entry |

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- **Backend:** Python, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, SQLite
- **Frontend:** React 18, Recharts, Axios, Lucide Icons
- **Styling:** Custom CSS (no UI library needed)

---

## 💡 Demo Scenario

1. Open Dashboard → See all crop price summaries
2. Go to Search → Type "Tomato" → See best market highlighted
3. Go to Trends → Select Tomato → View 7-day price chart
4. Go to Add Price → Submit a new crop price
5. Go to Alerts → See which crops had price spikes today